HEADWORD: Chalcidian
<hw>Chal*cid"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>chalcis</ets> a lizard, Gr. <grk>chalki`s</grk>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a tropical family of snakelike lizards
(<fam>Chalcid⟦ae⟧</fam>), having four small or rudimentary
legs.</def>⟦br⟧
